{# ### 4.1. outbound Attributes #}

{# #### `project_attributes_outbound_call_table_csv` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_outbound_call_table_csv",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Outbound - Call Table CSV [A]", "description": """**Important:** This attribute is going to be deprecated in future versions. Please use Widgets to
manage outbound CSV. To learn how to use Widgets for outbound CSV, please follow
[this guide](https://help.newo.ai/en/articles/13461654-outbound-calling-via-csv-list).

This attribute contains the CSV data for outbound calls.

Populate this attribute with content in CSV format to define the outbound call table.

Preferred CSV columns are:

- Phone number
- Reason to call

But it is possible to use any other columns as well. The agent will use this data to make outbound
calls. Agent will try to get phone numbers and reason to call based on the input content anyway.

Recommendations:

- Use header row in CSV to define column names to make it easier for the agent to identify the data.
- IMPORTANT! Ensure phone numbers are in a valid format (e.g., include country code). Otherwise, the
  agent might not be able to make the call.
- Keep the reason to call concise and clear. Otherwise, it might be interpreted incorrectly by the
  agent.
- IMPORTANT! Avoid putting duplicate phone numbers in the CSV. Otherwise, it will lead to issues
  with calling and call tracking.

The result of calling will be stored in another attribute called `Outbound - Calling Result CSV [A]`
(`project_attributes_outbound_call_table_csv_result`).

Example:

```csv
Phone Number,Reason to Call
+1234567890,Needs to be followed up regarding the recent purchase. Product: Laptop. Ask if they are satisfied with the service and if they have any questions
+1987654321,Check in regarding their account. Updates: Account has been successfully upgraded to premium status.
```""", "group": "4.1. Outbound", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": False }
)}}

