{# #### `project_attributes_setting_outbound_max_active_calls` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_outbound_max_active_calls",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Outbound - Max Active Calls [C]", "description": """This attribute defines the **upper limit of active call sessions** permitted to run simultaneously.
It serves as a critical governance mechanism for two primary purposes:

- **Platform Load Orchestration:** Prevents system resource exhaustion by capping the total
  processing demand at any given moment.
- **Integration Compliance:** Ensures outgoing and incoming traffic remains within the specific
  capacity limits defined by **NEWO Voice integrations**.

**Overflow Handling:**

When the defined limit is reached, any additional incoming call requests are not rejected. Instead,
they are placed into a **priority queue**. These queued calls are automatically executed in sequence
as soon as existing sessions conclude and capacity becomes available (i.e., when \"queue pressure\"
subsides).""", "group": "4.1. Outbound", "value_type": "number", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_setting_outbound_naive_conversation_deadline_seconds` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_setting_outbound_naive_conversation_deadline_seconds",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "Outbound - Conversation Start Deadline (Queue Timeout) [C]", "description": """This attribute defines the **maximum time, in seconds,** the system will wait for the
`conversation_started` event after an outbound call is placed.

- **Deadline-Based Waiting:** A timer starts when the call is queued or initiated. The system waits
  for `conversation_started` within this window.
- **Failure Handling:** If the event does not arrive before the deadline, the call is treated as
  **failed**.
- **Queue Cleanup:** Failed calls are removed from the queue so they do not occupy capacity or retry
  slots.""", "group": "4.1. Outbound", "value_type": "number", "is_hidden": True }
)}}

